Player_Romus

"We don't have a chance against this many. I will greet them from the palace balcony. I will try to calm them down or at least stall them."

Player_Romus

"We can't rely on outside help. We must get to the helipad ourselves. It is risky but it is our only way out of here."

Player_Romus

"We will just barricade ourselves here and hold until the help arrives. We have no choice but to wait."

Narrator

She was heavily pregnant and in no shape to run or act quickly.

Narrator

My guards looked at me for orders.

Player_Romus

"Come with me. I can't go out there without any guards."

Narrator

They saluted me and started following me around.

Narrator

I ran away from the door as soon as I could.

Narrator

With an explosion, the door opened right up. Two guards next to the door were not as fortunate as the others in the room.

I looked at Lucita and she had done the same.

Narrator

They were yelling at us to throw down our weapons.

Player_Romus_Italic

Shoot them.

Narrator

All I heard was a click. The magazine was empty.

Narrator

I shot the man in the front on the head. All rifles turned to me.

Player_Romus

"Please. I beg you. Don't hurt me."

Narrator

One of them took a step forward and shove the gun aside with his boots.

Narrator

Narrator

It was the guards that came back. They couldn't find anyone.

Narrator

I heard a few screams coming from the hallway as soon as we passed through. Guns were fired.

Player_Romus_Italic

We tried to sneak past without being seen.

Try to sneak past without being seen.

Narrator

We somehow managed to do it without attracting their attention.

Narrator

With a large explosion, the helicopter blew up along with our hopes of getting out of here.

Narrator

I squinted my eyes. They were planting what it looked like a bomb.

Player_Romus_Italic

I aimed carefully and fired my gun.

Aim carefully and fire.

Narrator

I shot the man planting the bomb in the head. The armed militant fell to the ground.

Narrator

When I came to my senses, I looked up. All of the enemies were dead.

Narrator

A guard on the ground was playing dead. He very slightly nodded.

Narrator

We had won. There was nothing in between us and the helicopter. But at what cost.

Narrator

I ripped off a piece from my shirt and wrapped it around Lucita's wound. She was bleeding profusely.

Narrator

I grabbed Lucita by the waist to support her and we started running.

Player_Romus

"It's okay. It is over. We are going to be fine. Just hang on."

Player_Romus

"We are almost out of here. I promise."

Narrator

Doors to the upper floor was right ahead. Armed assailants did not make it to this floor yet.

Player_Romus

"All I have done, I have done for this country. Nothing more."

Player_Romus

"All I have done, I have done for this country. Nothing more."

Player_Romus

"Blame the other Houses for this downfall."

Player_Romus

"Blame the other Houses for this downfall."

Player_Romus

"I thought I was right. But maybe I was not."

Player_Romus

"Fault lies within our system that created this situation."

Player_Romus

"People with the best intentions can sometimes be at places with the worst intentions."

Player_Romus

"You hold the future of this country in your hands."

Player_Romus

"Despite your calls, I will not abdicate. Because, only I can hear you this well, Rizia."

Player_Romus_Italic

I ducked and took cover.

Duck and take cover.

Silence fell on the crowd. It took a few dreadful seconds.

Player_Romus

"Please, listen to me. Fine. I will abdicate. Spare me and my family."

Narrator

I heard shots. Suddenly, I was on the ground.

Player_Romus

"You have won. But don't let this be in vain."

Narrator

They had gotten what they came here for.
